children.subject: @6623 said "The enrollment system will allow time conflicts between EE and EECS courses with other classes." So I'm really confused. Could the system be updated?

history.content: Time conflicts are allowed for all EE, EECS, and CS classes. I think the system may be sending this message in error. A student emailed me saying they were sent the same error message, but the lab they were trying to add is full. Please verify that that the lab you're trying to add is open and that the category of student you fall under is open. You can email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu if you have further questions.

children.subject:
I responded to the email you sent me directly.

EECS and CS seniors were given priority in Phase I. Students need to wait until their Phase II begins to change anything. Enough seats were added so that currently waitlisted EECS and CS seniors should be able to enroll.

Thanks! My section is full and now I cannot swap or drop and enroll in another section until my phase II, which is the 30th. I think the open sections are likely to run out again before then. I think it's a little unfair because I have been on the waitlist since my Phase I and no priority was given to seniors until now. Is there any way for me to change section now?

history.content: Hi, I'm a senior in my last semester and I need both 16A and another class to graduate. My other class's lec time conflicts with 16A's, and I got an email saying I cannot get off the waitlist of 16a because neither class allows time conflict enrollments. I think 16A has webcast and has been allowing time conflict enrollment for a long time. Could someone confirm the policy and tell me what to do?
